<item>
            <title>[SUREFIRE-857] Non-ASCII source and name in ReportEntry are escaped unicode on fork.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-857</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Non-ASCII source and name in ReportEntry are escaped unicode on fork. For example &apos;&#192;&apos;(A with grave) is replaced \u00C0.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;public class Escape&#192;Test {
    @Test
    public void test&#192;Test() {
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;XML report of this test class is following.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&amp;lt;testcase time=&quot;0.010&quot; classname=&quot;Escape\u00C0Test&quot; name=&quot;test\u00C0Test&quot;&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This problem is that &lt;b&gt;org.apache.maven.plugin.surefire.booterclient.outpu.ForkClient&lt;/b&gt; is not unescape for ReportEntry source and name. Because these are escaped with &lt;b&gt;org.apache.maven.surefire.booter.ForingRunListener&lt;/b&gt;, &lt;b&gt;ForkClient&lt;/b&gt; must be unescaped.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the attached patch for 2.12 I fixed this problem.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
