I think this behavior is much problem for non-ascii language region people.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m Japanese, so I usually use multibyte characters for test case methods.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;br/&gt;
see &lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/2316871&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gist.github.com/2316871&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Prior to version 2.9 (I&apos;ve confirmed at version 2.8.1), the result of the first case is good,&lt;br/&gt;
and from version 2.9 the result of that is escaped, and human-unreadable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I hope the patch the ticket owner attached will be applied as soon as possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
